nforcement agencies and regulatory agencies.            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark.text                        | Physical and behavioral evidence or signs that someone is being sexually abused are listed below:            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    .table-responsive                        table.table.table-bordered.mb-0                            thead                                tr                                    th Physical Evidence of abuse                                    th Behavioral signs of sexual abuse                            tbody                                tr                                    td Difficulty in walking                                    td Reluctance to be left alone with particular person                                tr                                    td Torn stained or bloody underwear                                    td Wearing lots of clothing especialty in bed                                tr                                    td pain or itching in genital area                                    td fear of touch                                tr                                    td Bruises or bleeding of the external genitalia                                    td Nightmares or fear at night                                tr                                    td Sexually transmitted diseases                                    td Apprehension when sex is brought up            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark.text                        | Reporting procedure. if you are aware of a suspect sexual abuse taking place, you must immediately report it to the DPCS or Administrator. If the suspected abuse is to an adult, you should report the abuse to your local or state Adult Protective Services (APS) Agency. If it is a child who is the victim, then you should  report the suspected abuse to your local or state child Abuse Agency. If you do not know who your state child abuse agency is you can call the Child Help's National Child Abuse hotline at 800-422-4453, TDD 800-222-4453, Appropriate family members should be notified of alleged instances of sexual abuse.TriUnion Healthcare shall report the alleged sexual abuse incident to its insurance agent.            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark.text                        | Anti Retaliation            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark.text                        | TriUnion Healthcare prohibits retaliation made against any employee, volunteer, board member or patient who reports a good faith complaint of sexual abuse or who participates in any related investigation. Making false accusations of sexual abuse in bad faith can have serious consequences for those who are wrongly accused. The organization prohibits making false and/or malicious sexual abuse allegations, as well as deliberately providing false information during an investigation. Anyone who violates this rule is subject to disciplinary action, up to and including termination.            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark.text                        | Investigation and follow-up            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark.text                        | TriUnion Healthcare will take all allegations of sexual abuse seriously and will promptly and thoroughly investigate whether sexual abuse has taken place. The organization will cooperate fully with any investigation conducted by law enforcement or other regulatory agencies. it is the organization's objective to conduct a fair and impartial investigation. The organization provides notice that they have the option of placing the accused on a leave of absence or on a reassignment to non-patient contract. The organization will make every reasonable effort to keep the matters involved in the allegation as confidential as possible while still allowing for a prompt and thorough investigation.            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark.text                        | Acknowledgement & Understanding of sexual Abuse Policy            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark.text                        | I acknowledge that i have received and read the sexual abuse policy and/or have had it explained to me. I understand that the organization will not tolerate any employee. volunteer board member or third party who commits sexual abuse. Disciplinary actions will be taken against those who are found to have commited sexual abuse.            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark.text                        | I understand that it is my responsibility to abide by all rules contained in the policy. I also understand how to report incidents of sexual abuse as seth forth in the abuse policy, including retaliating against my employee/volunteer exercising his/her rights under the policy.            .form-row.col-md-12                .form-group.col-md-12                    p.card-text.text-dark.text                        | I hereby attest that i understand my obligation to report sexual abuse as described above and will fullfill this obligation.            .form-row.col-12.float-right              .form-group.col-6.float-right              .form-group.col-md-6.text-center                  .card                      .card-body.bg-white                          div.flex.text-center                              div#sigbox(s